counters.name: critcount
counters.label: critical Fault
comment: Fault Counter

fv:FltCounter15min.label: current Fault Counter stats in 15 minute
comment: A class that represents the most current statistics for  Fault  Counter in a 15 minute sampling interval.  This class updates every 5 minutes.
Delete or ignore. For internal use only.
childAction.label: childAction

comment: The number of readings made within the current sample.
cnt.label: Number of Collections During this Interval

comment: Critical  Fault.  This is the average value read by the counter during the collection interval.  Note that this value resets to 0 at the beginning of each interval.
critcountAvg.label: critical Fault average value

comment: Critical  Fault.  This is the most current value read by the counter.
critcountLast.label: critical Fault current value

comment: Critical  Fault.  This is the largest value read by the counter during the collection interval.  This value is only overwritten if the most current value is larger than the previous value.  For example, if the value of the first reading is 3 and the value of the second reading is 4, the previous value is overwritten with 4.  If the third reading is smaller than 4, the value remains at 4.  Note that this value resets to 0 at the beginning of each interval.
critcountMax.label: critical Fault maximum value

comment: Critical  Fault.  This is the smallest value read by the counter during the collection interval.  This value is only overwritten if the most current value is smaller than the previous value.  For example, if the value of the first reading is 3 and the value of the second reading is 2, the previous value is overwritten with 2.  If the third reading is larger than 2, the value remains at 2.  Note that this value resets to 0 at the beginning of each interval.
critcountMin.label: critical Fault minimum value

comment: Critical  Fault.  This is the number of missed and/or incorrect values read by the counter during the collection interval.  Note that this value resets to 0 at the beginning of each interval.
critcountSpct.label: critical Fault suspect count

comment: Critical  Fault.  This indicates the properties of the counter that crossed the threshold during the collection interval.  Note that this value resets at the beginning of each interval.
critcountThr.label: critical Fault thresholded flags

comment: Critical  Fault.  This is the trending value of the counter.  Note that this value resets to 0 at the beginning of each interval.
critcountTr.label: critical Fault trend

comment: Critical  Fault.  This is the cumulative value of the counter from the previous collection interval.  Used for internal purposes.
critcountTrBase.label: critical Fault trend baseline

comment: Critical  Fault.  This is the total sum of all values read by the counter during the collection interval.  Note that this value resets to 0 at the beginning of each interval.
critcountTtl.label: critical Fault total sum
